quran[148]{c,v,t}:
  1,1,"In the Name of Allah‚ÄĒthe Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  1,2,All praise is for Allah‚ÄĒLord of all worlds
  1,3,"the Most Compassionate, Most Merciful"
  1,4,Master of the Day of Judgment
  1,5,You ňĻaloneňļ we worship and You ňĻaloneňļ we ask for help
  1,6,Guide us along the Straight Path
  1,7,"the Path of those You have blessed‚ÄĒnot those You are displeased with, or those who are astray"
  2,1,Alif-L√£m-Mń©m
  2,2,This is the Book! There is no doubt about it‚ÄĒa guide for those mindful ňĻof Allahňļ
  2,3,"who believe in the unseen,¬†establish prayer, and donate from what We have provided for them"
  2,4,"and who believe in what has been revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ¬†and what was revealed before you, and have sure faith in the Hereafter"
  2,5,"It is they who are ňĻtrulyňļ guided by their Lord, and it is they who will be successful"
  2,6,"As for those who persist in disbelief, it is the same whether you warn them or not‚ÄĒthey will never believe"
  2,7,"Allah has sealed their hearts and their hearing, and their sight is covered. They will suffer a tremendous punishment"
  2,8,"And there are some who say, ‚ÄúWe believe in Allah and the Last Day,‚ÄĚ yet they are not ňĻtrueňļ believers"
  2,9,"They seek to deceive Allah and the believers, yet they only deceive themselves, but they fail to perceive it"
  2,10,"There is sickness in their hearts, and Allah ňĻonlyňļ lets their sickness increase. They will suffer a painful punishment for their lies"
  2,11,"When they are told, ‚ÄúDo not spread corruption in the land,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúWe are only peace-makers!‚ÄĚ"
  2,12,"Indeed, it is they who are the corruptors, but they fail to perceive it"
  2,13,"And when they are told, ‚ÄúBelieve as others believe,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúWill we believe as the fools believe?‚ÄĚ Indeed, it is they who are fools, but they do not know"
  2,14,"When they meet the believers they say, ‚ÄúWe believe.‚ÄĚ But when alone with their evil associates they say, ‚ÄúWe are definitely with you; we were only mocking.‚ÄĚ"
  2,15,"Allah will throw their mockery back at them, leaving them to continue wandering blindly in their defiance"
  2,16,"They are the ones who trade guidance for misguidance. But this trade is profitless, and they are not ňĻrightlyňļ guided"
  2,17,"Their example is that of someone who kindles a fire, but when it lights up all around them, Allah takes away their light, leaving them in complete darkness‚ÄĒunable to see"
  2,18,"They are ňĻwilfullyňļ deaf, dumb, and blind, so they will never return ňĻto the Right Pathňļ"
  2,19,"Or ňĻthose caught inňļ a rainstorm from the sky with darkness, thunder, and lightning. They press their fingers into their ears at the sound of every thunder-clap for fear of death. And Allah encompasses the disbelievers ňĻby His mightňļ"
  2,20,"It is as if the lightning were about to snatch away their sight. Whenever lightning strikes, they walk in its light, but when darkness covers them, they stand still. Had Allah willed, He could have taken away their hearing and sight. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,21,"O humanity! Worship your Lord, Who created you and those before you, so that you may become mindful ňĻof Himňļ"
  2,22,"ňĻHe is the Oneňļ Who has made the earth a place of settlement for you and the sky a canopy; and sends down rain from the sky, causing fruits to grow as a provision for you. So do not knowingly set up equals to Allah ňĻin worshipňļ"
  2,23,"And if you are in doubt about what We have revealed to Our servant,¬†then produce a s√Ľrah¬†like it and call your helpers other than Allah, if what you say is true"
  2,24,"But if you are unable to do so‚ÄĒand you will never be able to do so‚ÄĒthen fear the Fire fuelled with people and stones, which is prepared for the disbelievers"
  2,25,"Give good news ňĻO Prophetňļ to those who believe and do good that they will have Gardens under which rivers flow. Whenever provided with fruit, they will say, ‚ÄúThis is what we were given before,‚ÄĚ for they will be served fruit that looks similar ňĻbut tastes differentňļ. They will have pure spouses,¬†and they will be there forever"
  2,26,"Surely Allah does not shy away from using the parable of a mosquito or what is even smaller. As for the believers, they know that it is the truth from their Lord. And as for the disbelievers, they argue, ‚ÄúWhat does Allah mean by such a parable?‚ÄĚ Through this ňĻtestňļ, He leaves many to stray, and guides many. And He leaves none to stray except the rebellious‚ÄĒ"
  2,27,"those who violate Allah‚Äôs covenant after it has been affirmed, break whatever ňĻtiesňļ Allah has ordered to be maintained, and spread corruption in the land. It is they who are the ňĻtrueňļ losers"
  2,28,"How can you deny Allah? You were lifeless and He gave you life, then He will cause you to die and again bring you to life, and then to Him you will ňĻallňļ be returned"
  2,29,"He is the One Who created everything in the earth for you. Then He turned towards the heaven, forming it into seven heavens. And He has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of all things"
  2,30,"ňĻRememberňļ when your Lord said to the angels, ‚ÄúI am going to place a successive ňĻhumanňļ authority on earth.‚ÄĚ They asked ňĻAllahňļ, ‚ÄúWill You place in it someone who will spread corruption there and shed blood while we glorify Your praises and proclaim Your holiness?‚ÄĚ Allah responded, ‚ÄúI know what you do not know.‚ÄĚ"
  2,31,"He taught Adam the names of all things, then He presented them to the angels and said, ‚ÄúTell Me the names of these, if what you say is true?‚ÄĚ"
  2,32,"They replied, ‚ÄúGlory be to You! We have no knowledge except what You have taught us. You are truly the All-Knowing, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  2,33,"Allah said, ‚ÄúO Adam! Inform them of their names.‚ÄĚ Then when Adam did, Allah said, ‚ÄúDid I not tell you that I know the secrets of the heavens and the earth, and I know what you reveal and what you conceal?‚ÄĚ"
  2,34,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We said to the angels, ‚ÄúProstrate before Adam,‚ÄĚ¬†so they all did‚ÄĒbut not Ibl√ģs,¬†who refused and acted arrogantly,¬†becoming unfaithful"
  2,35,"We cautioned, ‚ÄúO Adam! Live with your wife in Paradise and eat as freely as you please, but do not approach this tree, or else you will be wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  2,36,"But Satan deceived them‚ÄĒleading to their fall from the ňĻblissfulňļ state they were in,¬†and We said, ‚ÄúDescend from the heavens ňĻto the earthňļ as enemies to each other.¬†You will find in the earth a residence and provision for your appointed stay.‚ÄĚ"
  2,37,"Then Adam was inspired with words ňĻof prayerňļ by his Lord,¬†so He accepted his repentance. Surely He is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,38,"We said, ‚ÄúDescend all of you! Then when guidance comes to you from Me, whoever follows it, there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,39,But those who disbelieve and deny Our signs will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever.‚ÄĚ
  2,40,"O children of Israel!¬†Remember My favours upon you. Fulfil your covenant and I will fulfil Mine, and stand in awe of Me ňĻaloneňļ"
  2,41,Believe in My revelations which confirm your Scriptures.¬†Do not be the first to deny them or trade them for a fleeting gain.¬†And be mindful of Me
  2,42,Do not mix truth with falsehood or hide the truth knowingly
  2,43,"Establish prayer, pay alms-tax,¬†and bow down with those who bow down"
  2,44,"Do you preach righteousness and fail to practice it yourselves, although you read the Scripture? Do you not understand"
  2,45,"And seek help through patience and prayer. Indeed, it is a burden except for the humble‚ÄĒ"
  2,46,those who are certain that they will meet their Lord and to Him they will return
  2,47,O Children of Israel! Remember ňĻallňļ the favours I granted you and how I honoured you above the others
  2,48,"Guard yourselves against the Day on which no soul will be of help to another. No intercession¬†will be accepted, no ransom taken, and no help will be given"
  2,49,"ňĻRememberňļ how We delivered you from the people of Pharaoh, who afflicted you with dreadful torment, slaughtering your sons and keeping your women. That was a severe test from your Lord"
  2,50,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We parted the sea, rescued you, and drowned Pharaoh‚Äôs people before your very eyes"
  2,51,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We appointed forty nights for Moses, then you worshipped the calf in his absence, acting wrongfully"
  2,52,Even then We ňĻstillňļ forgave you so perhaps you would be grateful
  2,53,And ňĻrememberňļ when We gave Moses the Scripture‚ÄĒthe standard ňĻto distinguish between right and wrongňļ that perhaps you would be ňĻrightlyňļ guided
  2,54,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Moses said to his people, ‚ÄúO my people! Surely you have wronged yourselves by worshipping the calf, so turn in repentance to your Creator and execute ňĻthe calf-worshippers amongňļ yourselves. That is best for you in the sight of your Creator.‚ÄĚ Then He accepted your repentance. Surely He is the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,55,"And ňĻrememberňļ when you said, ‚ÄúO Moses! We will never believe you until we see Allah with our own eyes,‚ÄĚ so a thunderbolt struck you while you were looking on"
  2,56,"Then We brought you back to life after your death, so that perhaps you would be grateful"
  2,57,"And ňĻremember whenňļ We shaded you with clouds and sent down to you manna and quails,¬†ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúEat from the good things We have provided for you.‚ÄĚ The evildoers ňĻcertainlyňļ did not wrong Us, but wronged themselves"
  2,58,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We said, ‚ÄúEnter this city and eat freely from wherever you please; enter the gate with humility, saying, ‚ÄėAbsolve us.‚Äô We will forgive your sins and multiply the reward for the good-doers.‚ÄĚ"
  2,59,But the wrongdoers changed the words they were commanded to say. So We sent down a punishment from the heavens upon them for their rebelliousness
  2,60,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Moses prayed for water for his people, We said, ‚ÄúStrike the rock with your staff.‚ÄĚ Then twelve springs gushed out, ňĻandňļ each tribe knew its drinking place. ňĻWe then said,ňļ ‚ÄúEat and drink of Allah‚Äôs provisions, and do not go about spreading corruption in the land.‚ÄĚ"
  2,61,"And ňĻrememberňļ when you said, ‚ÄúO Moses! We cannot endure the same meal ňĻevery dayňļ. So ňĻjustňļ call upon your Lord on our behalf, He will bring forth for us some of what the earth produces of herbs, cucumbers, garlic, lentils, and onions.‚ÄĚ Moses scolded ňĻthemňļ, ‚ÄúDo you exchange what is better for what is worse? ňĻYou canňļ go down to any village and you will find what you have asked for.‚ÄĚ They were stricken with disgrace and misery, and they invited the displeasure of Allah for rejecting Allah‚Äôs signs and unjustly killing the prophets. This is ňĻa fair rewardňļ for their disobedience and violations"
  2,62,"Indeed, the believers, Jews, Christians, and Sabians‚ÄĒwhoever ňĻtrulyňļ believes in Allah and the Last Day and does good will have their reward with their Lord. And there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,63,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took a covenant from you and raised the mountain above you ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúHold firmly to that ňĻScriptureňļ which We have given you and observe its teachings so perhaps you will become mindful ňĻof Allahňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  2,64,"Yet you turned away afterwards. Had it not been for Allah‚Äôs grace and mercy upon you, you would have certainly been of the losers"
  2,65,"You are already aware of those of you who broke the Sabbath. We said to them, ‚ÄúBe disgraced apes!‚ÄĚ"
  2,66,"So We made their fate an example to present and future generations, and a lesson to the God-fearing"
  2,67,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Moses said to his people, ‚ÄúAllah commands you to sacrifice a cow.‚ÄĚ¬†They replied, ‚ÄúAre you mocking us?‚ÄĚ Moses responded, ‚ÄúI seek refuge in Allah from acting foolishly!‚ÄĚ"
  2,68,"They said, ‚ÄúCall upon your Lord to clarify for us what type ňĻof cowňļ it should be!‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúAllah says, ‚ÄėThe cow should neither be old nor young but in between. So do as you are commanded!‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  2,69,"They said, ‚ÄúCall upon your Lord to specify for us its colour.‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúAllah says, ‚ÄėIt should be a bright yellow cow‚ÄĒpleasant to see.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  2,70,"Again they said, ‚ÄúCall upon your Lord so that He may make clear to us which cow, for all cows look the same to us. Then, Allah willing, we will be guided ňĻto the right oneňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  2,71,"He replied, ‚ÄúAllah says, ‚ÄėIt should have been used neither to till the soil nor water the fields; wholesome and without blemish.‚Äô‚ÄĚ They said, ‚ÄúNow you have come with the truth.‚ÄĚ Yet they still slaughtered it hesitantly"
  2,72,"ňĻThis isňļ when a man was killed and you disputed who the killer was, but Allah revealed what you concealed"
  2,73,"So We instructed, ‚ÄúStrike the dead body with a piece of the cow.‚ÄĚ This is how ňĻeasilyňļ Allah brings the dead to life, showing you His signs so that you may understand"
  2,74,"Even then your hearts became hardened like a rock or even harder, for some rocks gush rivers; others split, spilling water; while others are humbled in awe of Allah. And Allah is never unaware of what you do"
  2,75,"Do you ňĻbelievers stillňļ expect them to be true to you, though a group of them would hear the word of Allah then knowingly corrupt it after understanding it"
  2,76,"When they meet the believers they say, ‚ÄúWe believe.‚ÄĚ But in private they say ňĻto each otherňļ, ‚ÄúWill you disclose to the believers the knowledge Allah has revealed to you,¬†so that they may use it against you before your Lord? Do you not understand?‚ÄĚ"
  2,77,Do they not know that Allah is aware of what they conceal and what they reveal
  2,78,"And among them are the illiterate who know nothing about the Scripture except lies, and ňĻsoňļ they ňĻwishfullyňļ speculate"
  2,79,"So woe¬†to those who distort the Scripture with their own hands then say, ‚ÄúThis is from Allah‚ÄĚ‚ÄĒseeking a fleeting gain! So woe to them for what their hands have written, and woe to them for what they have earned"
  2,80,"ňĻSome ofňļ the Jews claim, ‚ÄúThe Fire will not touch us except for a number of days.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúHave you taken a pledge from Allah‚ÄĒfor Allah never breaks His word‚ÄĒor are you ňĻjustňļ saying about Allah what you do not know?‚ÄĚ"
  2,81,But no! Those who commit evil and are engrossed in sin will be the residents of the Fire. They will be there forever
  2,82,And those who believe and do good will be the residents of Paradise. They will be there forever
  2,83,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took a covenant from the children of Israel ňĻstatingňļ, ‚ÄúWorship none but Allah; be kind to parents, relatives, orphans and the needy; speak kindly to people; establish prayer; and pay alms-tax.‚ÄĚ But you ňĻIsraelitesňļ turned away‚ÄĒexcept for a few of you‚ÄĒand were indifferent"
  2,84,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We took your covenant that you would neither shed each other‚Äôs blood nor expel each other from their homes, you gave your pledge and bore witness"
  2,85,"But here you are, killing each other and expelling some of your people from their homes, aiding one another in sin and aggression; and when those ňĻexpelledňļ come to you as captives, you still ransom them‚ÄĒthough expelling them was unlawful for you.¬†Do you believe in some of the Scripture and reject the rest? Is there any reward for those who do so among you other than disgrace in this worldly life and being subjected to the harshest punishment on the Day of Judgment? For Allah is never unaware of what you do"
  2,86,"These are the ones who trade the Hereafter for the life of this world. So their punishment will not be reduced, nor will they be helped"
  2,87,"Indeed, We gave Moses the Book and sent after him successive messengers. And We gave Jesus, son of Mary, clear proofs and supported him with the holy spirit.¬†Why is it that every time a messenger comes to you ňĻIsraelitesňļ with something you do not like, you become arrogant, rejecting some and killing others"
  2,88,"They say, ‚ÄúOur hearts are unreceptive!‚ÄĚ¬†In fact, Allah has condemned them for their disbelief. They have but little faith"
  2,89,"Although they used to pray for victory ňĻby means of the Prophetňļ over the polytheists,¬†when there came to them a Book from Allah which they recognized,¬†confirming the Scripture they had ňĻin their handsňļ, they rejected it. So may Allah‚Äôs condemnation be upon the disbelievers"
  2,90,Miserable is the price they have sold their souls for‚ÄĒdenying Allah‚Äôs revelation and resenting Allah for granting His grace to whoever He wills of His servants! They have earned wrath upon wrath. And such disbelievers will suffer a humiliating punishment
  2,91,"When it is said to them: ‚ÄúBelieve in what Allah has revealed,‚ÄĚ they reply, ‚ÄúWe only believe in what was sent down to us,‚ÄĚ and they deny what came afterwards, though it is the truth confirming their own Scriptures! Ask ňĻthem, O Prophetňļ, ‚ÄúWhy then did you kill Allah‚Äôs prophets before, if you are ňĻtrulyňļ believers?‚ÄĚ"
  2,92,"Indeed, Moses came to you with clear proofs, then you worshipped the calf in his absence, acting wrongfully"
  2,93,"And when We took your covenant and raised the mountain above you ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúHold firmly to that ňĻScriptureňļ which We have given you and obey,‚ÄĚ they answered, ‚ÄúWe hear and disobey.‚ÄĚ The love of the calf was rooted in their hearts because of their disbelief. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúHow evil is what your ňĻso-calledňļ belief prompts you to do, if you ňĻactuallyňļ believe ňĻin the Torahňļ!‚ÄĚ"
  2,94,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIf the ňĻeternalňļ Home of the Hereafter with Allah is exclusively for you ňĻIsraelitesňļ out of all humanity, then wish for death if what you say is true!‚ÄĚ"
  2,95,But they will never wish for that because of what their hands have done.¬†And Allah has ňĻperfectňļ knowledge of the wrongdoers
  2,96,"You will surely find them clinging to life more eagerly than any other people, even more than polytheists. Each one of them wishes to live a thousand years. But even if they were to live that long, it would not save them from the punishment. And Allah is All-Seeing of what they do"
  2,97,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúWhoever is an enemy of Gabriel should know that he revealed this ňĻQuranňļ to your heart by Allah‚Äôs Will, confirming what came before it‚ÄĒa guide and good news for the believers.‚ÄĚ"
  2,98,"Whoever is an enemy of Allah, His angels, His messengers, Gabriel, and Michael, then ňĻlet them know thatňļ Allah is certainly the enemy of the disbelievers"
  2,99,"Indeed, We have sent down to you ňĻO Prophetňļ clear revelations. ňĻButňļ none will deny them except the rebellious"
  2,100,"Why is it that every time they make a covenant, a group of them casts it aside? In fact, most of them do not believe"
  2,101,"Now, when a messenger from Allah has come to them‚ÄĒconfirming their own Scriptures‚ÄĒsome of the People of the Book cast the Book of Allah behind their backs as if they did not know"
  2,102,"They ňĻinsteadňļ followed the magic promoted by the devils during the reign of Solomon. Never did Solomon disbelieve, rather the devils disbelieved. They taught magic to the people, along with what had been revealed to the two angels, H√Ęr√Ľt and M√Ęr√Ľt, in Babylon.¬†The two angels never taught anyone without saying, ‚ÄúWe are only a test ňĻfor youňļ, so do not abandon ňĻyourňļ faith.‚ÄĚ Yet people learned ňĻmagicňļ that caused a rift ňĻevenňļ between husband and wife; although their magic could not harm anyone except by Allah‚Äôs Will. They learned what harmed them and did not benefit them‚ÄĒalthough they already knew that whoever buys into magic would have no share in the Hereafter. Miserable indeed was the price for which they sold their souls, if only they knew"
  2,103,"If only they were faithful and mindful ňĻof Allahňļ, there would have been a better reward from Allah, if only they knew"
  2,104,"O believers! Do not say, ‚ÄúR√Ę‚Äôina.‚ÄĚ [Herd us!] But say, ‚ÄúUnŠļďurna,‚ÄĚ [Tend to us!] and listen ňĻattentivelyňļ.¬†And the disbelievers will suffer a painful punishment"
  2,105,"The disbelievers from the People of the Book and the polytheists would not want you to receive any blessing from your Lord, but Allah selects whoever He wills for His mercy. And Allah is the Lord of infinite bounty"
  2,106,"If We ever abrogate¬†a verse or cause it to be forgotten, We replace it with a better or similar one. Do you not know that Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,107,"Do you not know that the kingdom of the heavens and the earth belongs ňĻonlyňļ to Allah, and you have no guardian or helper besides Allah"
  2,108,Or do you ňĻbelieversňļ intend to ask of your Messenger as Moses was asked before?¬†But whoever trades belief for disbelief has truly strayed from the Right Way
  2,109,"Many among the People of the Book wish they could turn you ňĻbelieversňļ back to disbelief because of their envy, after the truth has been made clear to them. Pardon and bear with them until Allah delivers His decision. Surely Allah is Most Capable of everything"
  2,110,"Establish prayer, and pay alms-tax. Whatever good you send forth for yourselves, you will ňĻcertainlyňļ find ňĻits rewardňļ with Allah. Surely Allah is All-Seeing of what you do"
  2,111,"The Jews and Christians each claim that none will enter Paradise except those of their own faith. These are their desires. Reply, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúShow ňĻmeňļ your proof if what you say is true.‚ÄĚ"
  2,112,"But no! Whoever submits themselves to Allah and does good will have their reward with their Lord. And there will be no fear for them, nor will they grieve"
  2,113,"The Jews say, ‚ÄúThe Christians have nothing to stand on‚ÄĚ and the Christians say, ‚ÄúThe Jews have nothing to stand on,‚ÄĚ although both recite the Scriptures. And those ňĻpagansňļ who have no knowledge say the same ňĻabout people of faithňļ. Surely Allah will judge between them on the Day of Judgment regarding their dispute"
  2,114,"Who does more wrong than those who prevent Allah‚Äôs Name from being mentioned in His places of worship and strive to destroy them? Such people have no right to enter these places except with fear.¬†For them is disgrace in this world, and they will suffer a tremendous punishment in the Hereafter"
  2,115,"To Allah belong the east and the west, so wherever you turn you are facing ňĻtowardsňļ Allah.¬†Surely Allah is All-Encompassing,¬†All-Knowing"
  2,116,"They¬†say, ‚ÄúAllah has offspring.‚ÄĚ¬†Glory be to Him! In fact, to Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and the earth‚ÄĒall are subject to His Will"
  2,117,"ňĻHe isňļ the Originator of the heavens and the earth! When He decrees a matter, He simply tells it, ‚ÄúBe!‚ÄĚ And it is"
  2,118,"Those who have no knowledge say, ‚ÄúIf only Allah would speak to us or a sign would come to us!‚ÄĚ The same was said by those who came before. Their hearts are all alike. Indeed, We have made the signs clear for people of sure faith"
  2,119,We have surely sent you with the truth ňĻO Prophetňļ as a deliverer of good news and a warner. And you will not be accountable for the residents of the Hellfire
  2,120,"Never will the Jews or Christians be pleased with you, until you follow their faith. Say, ‚ÄúAllah‚Äôs guidance is the only ňĻtrueňļ guidance.‚ÄĚ And if you were to follow their desires after ňĻallňļ the knowledge that has come to you, there would be none to protect or help you against Allah"
  2,121,"Those We have given the Book follow it as it should be followed. It is they who ňĻtrulyňļ believe in it. As for those who reject it, it is they who are the losers"
  2,122,O Children of Israel! Remember My favours upon you and how I honoured you above the others
  2,123,"And guard yourselves against the Day when no soul will be of any help to another. No ransom will be taken, no intercession accepted, and no help will be given"
  2,124,"ňĻRememberňļ when Abraham was tested by his Lord with ňĻcertainňļ commandments, which he fulfilled. Allah said, ‚ÄúI will certainly make you into a role model for the people.‚ÄĚ Abraham asked, ‚ÄúWhat about my offspring?‚ÄĚ Allah replied, ‚ÄúMy covenant is not extended to the wrongdoers.‚ÄĚ"
  2,125,"And ňĻrememberňļ when We made the Sacred House¬†a centre and a sanctuary for the people ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúňĻYou mayňļ take the standing-place of Abraham¬†as a site of prayer.‚ÄĚ And We entrusted Abraham and Ishmael to purify My House for those who circle it, who meditate in it, and who bow and prostrate themselves ňĻin prayerňļ"
  2,126,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham said, ‚ÄúMy Lord, make this city ňĻof Meccaňļ secure and provide fruits to its people‚ÄĒthose among them who believe in Allah and the Last Day.‚ÄĚ He answered, ‚ÄúAs for those who disbelieve, I will let them enjoy themselves for a little while, then I will condemn them to the torment of the Fire. What an evil destination!‚ÄĚ"
  2,127,"And ňĻrememberňļ when Abraham raised the foundation of the House with Ishmael, ňĻboth praying,ňļ ‚ÄúOur Lord! Accept ňĻthisňļ from us. You are indeed the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,128,"Our Lord! Make us both ňĻfullyňļ submit to You¬†and from our descendants a nation that will submit to you. Show us our rituals, and turn to us in grace. You are truly the Accepter of Repentance, Most Merciful"
  2,129,"Our Lord! Raise from among them a messenger who will recite to them Your revelations, teach them the Book and wisdom, and purify them. Indeed, You ňĻaloneňļ are the Almighty, All-Wise.‚ÄĚ"
  2,130,"And who would reject the faith of Abraham except a fool! We certainly chose him in this life, and in the Hereafter he will surely be among the righteous"
  2,131,"When his Lord ordered him, ‚ÄúSubmit ňĻto My Willňļ,‚ÄĚ he responded, ‚ÄúI submit to the Lord of all worlds.‚ÄĚ"
  2,132,"This was the advice of Abraham‚ÄĒas well as Jacob‚ÄĒto his children, ňĻsayingňļ, ‚ÄúIndeed, Allah has chosen for you this faith; so do not die except in ňĻa state of fullňļ submission.‚ÄĚ"
  2,133,"Or did you witness when death came to Jacob? He asked his children, ‚ÄúWho will you worship after my passing?‚ÄĚ They replied, ‚ÄúWe will ňĻcontinue toňļ worship your God, the God of your forefathers‚ÄĒAbraham, Ishmael, and Isaac‚ÄĒthe One God. And to Him we ňĻallňļ submit.‚ÄĚ"
  2,134,That was a community that had already gone before. For them is what they earned and for you is what you have earned. And you will not be accountable for what they have done
  2,135,"The Jews and Christians each say, ‚ÄúFollow our faith to be ňĻrightlyňļ guided.‚ÄĚ Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúNo! We follow the faith of Abraham, the upright‚ÄĒwho was not a polytheist.‚ÄĚ"
  2,136,"Say, ňĻO believers,ňļ ‚ÄúWe believe in Allah and what has been revealed to us; and what was revealed to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants; and what was given to Moses, Jesus, and other prophets from their Lord. We make no distinction between any of them. And to Allah we all submit.‚ÄĚ"
  2,137,"So if they believe in what you believe, then they will indeed be ňĻrightlyňļ guided. But if they turn away, they are simply opposed ňĻto the truthňļ. But Allah will spare you their evil. For He is the All-Hearing, All-Knowing"
  2,138,This is the ňĻnaturalňļ Way of Allah. And who is better than Allah in ordaining a way? And we worship ňĻnone butňļ Him
  2,139,"Say, ‚ÄúWould you dispute with us about Allah, while He is our Lord and your Lord? We are accountable for our deeds and you for yours. And we are devoted to Him ňĻaloneňļ"
  2,140,"Do you claim that Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and his descendants were all Jews or Christians?‚ÄĚ Say, ‚ÄúWho is more knowledgeable: you or Allah?‚ÄĚ Who does more wrong than those who hide the testimony they received from Allah? And Allah is never unaware of what you do"
  2,141,That was a community that had already gone before. For them is what they earned and for you is what you have earned. And you will not be accountable for what they have done